rst Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Gant was born about 1148, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Gilbert de Gant 1st Earl of Lincoln, was 23 and her mother, Rohese de Clare, was 26. She married Simon de Senlis III about 1163, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1185, in Bridlington, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 38."},"et":{"Abt 1148–1185":"umbes 1148–1185","1148–1185":"1148–1185","1145–1184":"1145–1184","1163–1184":"1163–1184","1165–1250":"1165–1250","1126–1156":"1126–1156","1124–1175":"1124–1175","1165":"1165","1175":"1175","Abt 1148":"umbes 1148","Abt June 1184":"umbes juuni 1184","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1250":"1250","1184":"1184","Abt 1163":"umbes 1163","Bef 1184":"enne 1184","1126":"1126","1148":"1148","1124":"1124","1156":"1156","1145":"1145","Abt 1165":"umbes 1165","about 1148":"umbes 1148","about 1163":"umbes 1163","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warkworth, Northamptonshire, England":"Warkworth, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bridlington, Yorkshire, England":"Bridlington, Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Li